      <span class="post-breadcrumb-sep">›</span>
      <span>Blue Hour Holiday Portraits</span>
    </nav>
    <span class="post-tag">Family · Holiday · Mini Sessions</span>
    <h1 class="post-title">Blue Hour Front-Yard<br>Holiday Portraits</h1>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.2rem;font-weight:300;font-style:italic;color:var(--muted);margin-top:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">A Simple, Beautiful Way to Save the Season</p>
    <div class="post-meta">
      <span>Palanivel</span>
      <span class="blog-meta-dot" style="width:3px;height:3px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--muted-dark);"></span>
      <span>December 9, 2025</span>
      <span class="blog-meta-dot" style="width:3px;height:3px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--muted-dark);"></span>
      <span>3 min read</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Hero Image ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div style="max-width:900px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 var(--gutter);">
    <div class="post-img">
      <Image src={aboutMain} alt="Blue hour holiday family portraits in front yard Katy TX" loading="eager" style="background:var(--surface-2);" fetchpriority="high" width={900} height={506} />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Post Body ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <article class="post-body">

    <p>The holidays are here, your lights are up, and the evenings feel warm and cozy. This is one of the best times of the year to get family photos — and you don't even have to leave your home.</p>

    <h2>What Is Blue Hour?</h2>
    <p>Blue hour is the short window right after sunset when the sky turns a deep, rich blue and your holiday lights begin to glow. It's soft, calm, and genuinely magical for photography. Not too bright, not too dark — just enough natural light to keep your faces clear while the lights in your background start to shine.</p>

    <div class="post-pullquote">
      <p>Blue hour + holiday lights = simple, beautiful photos that feel real. This is something you simply cannot replicate during the day.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Why Your Front Yard?</h2>
    <p>Many families assume good photos only happen in studios or carefully chosen locations. But your own home can give you the warmest, most personal backdrop of all. Your front yard has your holiday lights, your decorations, your home in the background — your family's real space and real memories.</p>
    <p>Years from now, these are the photos that will feel the most meaningful. Not because they were taken somewhere beautiful, but because they show your life. Your home. Your people, exactly as they were.</p>

    <h2>How Your Lights Do the Work</h2>
    <p>As the sky deepens and your lights turn on, something changes. The photos gain a warm glow, soft little highlights settle around your family, and the whole scene takes on that cozy holiday feeling that's impossible to fake in a studio. The result is what photographers call a high-key holiday style — clean, bright, genuinely festive.</p>

    <h2>Short Sessions That Fit the Season</h2>
    <p>The holidays are busy. These sessions are designed to be quick, easy, and completely stress-free.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>I come to your front yard — no driving, no parking, no rushing</li>
      <li>We shoot for 15–20 minutes</li>
      <li>You receive 5 fully edited, full-resolution images</li>
      <li>Additional images available at $20 each</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Just step outside with your family, smile for a few minutes, and enjoy the moment. That's it.</p>

    <h2>What You'll Receive</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>5 fully edited, full-resolution photos delivered via private gallery</li>
      <li>Clean, warm holiday glow — our signature cinematic editing</li>
      <li>Front-yard setup using your existing lights and decorations</li>
      <li>Easy digital download — no watermarks</li>
      <li>Option to add extra images or order prints through your gallery</li>
    </ul>

    <p>These images are perfect for holiday cards, WhatsApp, social media, family albums, and quick gifts for grandparents who live far away.</p>

    <h2>Why Families Love This Style</h2>
    <p>You stay in your comfort zone — right at home. Kids are naturally calmer and more themselves. No heavy outfits or formal looks required. The soft glow of your own lights makes everyone look beautiful. And your own holiday décor becomes part of the story.</p>
    <p>It's simple, honest, and warm — which is exactly what NiO Pictures is built on.</p>

    <div class="post-divider"></div>

    <div class="post-cta">
      <h3>Book a Holiday Mini-Session</h3>
      <p>Holiday evenings fill up quickly — especially weekends. Grab your spot before they're gone.</p>
      <a href="https://niopictures.pixieset.com/booking/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary btn-arrow">Book a Mini-Session</a>
      <a href="/family-photography-katy-tx.html" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-left:0.5rem;">Full Family Sessions</a>
    </div>

  </article>

